-- Kenya Probe Finds Chopper Crash That Killed Minister an Accident
-- B y   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 2013-02-28T15:06:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-28/kenya-probe-finds-chopper-crash-that-killed-minister-an-accident.html
Cause of crash was “loss of
aircraft control in poor visibility” chairwoman of commission
of inquiry, Judge Kalpana Rawal, tells reporters in capital,
Nairobi.
* Postmortem poorly done, death caused by carbon monoxide
poisoning, traumatic, fire injuries, Rawal says
* NOTE: Kenyan Internal Security Minister George Saitoti,
Assistant Internal Security Minister Orwa Ojode, two pilots and
two bodyguards died when  aircraft crashed in Ngong Forest on
outskirts of Nairobi on June 10  To contact the reporter on this story:
